entry.title: Tropical Storm Hilary Makes Landfall in Mexico, Threatening Southern California
entry.content: Hilary is on a track that forecasters say is likely to bring drenching rains beyond California into Nevada and even as far north as Boise, Idaho, over the next two days. As rains started to pelt the region, a number of earthquakes between 2.8 and 5.1 magnitude occurred near Ojai, Calif.
